# User Roles

## Admin

Admin users manage the platform.

Permissions:

* Create courses
* Add lessons
* Edit or delete courses
* Upload Vimeo video links
* Manage students
* View analytics

## Student

Students use the platform to learn.

Permissions:

* Register account
* Login
* Browse courses
* Enroll in courses
* Watch lessons
* Track course progress

---

# Core Features

## 1. Homepage

The homepage introduces the platform and displays available courses.

Sections:

* Hero section
* Featured courses
* Course categories
* Call to action
* Footer

---

## 2. Courses Page

Displays all courses available on the platform.

Each course card should include:

* Course thumbnail
* Course title
* Short description
* Number of lessons
* Instructor name
* Enroll button

---

## 3. Course Details Page

Course details should include:

* Course title
* Instructor
* Description
* Course thumbnail
* Total lessons
* Course curriculum (lesson list)
* Enroll button

---

## 4. Student Dashboard

Students should have a personal dashboard where they can manage their learning.

Features:

* My Courses
* Continue Learning
* Progress tracking
* Completed lessons

---

## 5. Lesson Player Page

This is the main learning interface.

Layout:

Left Sidebar:

* Lesson list
* Course structure

Main Content:

* Vimeo video player
* Lesson title
* Lesson description
* Next lesson button

The video player must use Vimeo embedded player.

Example embed:

https://player.vimeo.com/video/{video_id}

Students should only see the clean video player without Vimeo branding or external links.

---

## 6. Admin Dashboard

Admin dashboard allows course management.

Features:

Create Course
Fields:

* Title
* Description
* Price
* Thumbnail

Add Lessons
Fields:

* Lesson title
* Description
* Vimeo video URL
* Lesson order
* Duration

Admin can:

* Edit lessons
* Delete lessons
* Manage course structure

